Enum Constant Detail

Queued

public static final Result.Status Queued
Indicates that the request was accepted and passed validation, but it was given to another system and we do not know when it will be committed. If possible the connector should also return a token for tracking.

This is the default status, if no result object is returned or if the result object is missing a status, it can be assumed to have been queued.

Committed

public static final Result.Status Committed
Indicates that the request was fully processed and the changes are known to have been made. The caller can use this to immediately update an external model to reflect the changes rather than waiting for a later aggregation.

Failed

public static final Result.Status Failed
Indicates that the request was not processed due to a fatal error. The connector should save one or more messages on the message list.

Retry

public static final Result.Status Retry
Indicates that the request was not processed due to a non fatal error and that it should be retried at a later time. The connector can also set the retryInterval property to indicate the preferred wait time.
